# BentoBox Component Implementation

## Component Structure
The BentoBox component is implemented in [src/components/BentoBox.tsx](mdc:src/components/BentoBox.tsx) and consists of:

### Layout
- Two rows on the left (one if a dress is in the outfit)
- Three Rows on the right for Outerwear, Accessories, and shoes in that order
- The Accessories and Outerwear rows should hold two items when two clothing objects are recommended
- Currently the minimum viable product has this box as static while the final functionality will have elements expand when clicked

## Grid Organization

### Left Column
- Top item (48% height)
- Bottom item (48% height)
- Margin gap between items
- Dress option (100% height when used)

### Right Column
- Outerwear (stacked horizontally)
- Accessories (stacked vertically)
- Shoes (bottom right, aligned with bottom)

## Element Implementation

### BentoBoxElement
- Light gray background
- Square with rounded edges
- No outlines
- Vertical labels (rotated 90°)
- Vector/PNG icons (black, no background)

### Label Styling
- Very light gray
- Italic Montserrat font
- Left side positioning
- Transform origin: '0% 0%'

## Animation and Interaction

### Expansion Animation (not currently implemented)
- Smooth width/height transitions
- Animated.Value for both dimensions
- Proper z-index management
- Push other elements offscreen

### Touch Handling
- Single tap for expansion
- When expanded, single tap for Smooth collapse animation
- Proper event propagation

